/**
@defgroup unit_tests Unit tests
@brief CMocka-based unit tests for the LAME library and frontend.

The tests under @c test/unit exercise individual functions in isolation using
the [CMocka](https://cmocka.org/) framework. They are optional: the build only
compiles and runs them when configured with

@code
./configure --enable-unit-tests
@endcode

(default off). With the flag set, @c "make check" builds and runs every test
under @c test/unit and reports each one's pass/fail status. Only the pre-2.0 CMocka macro set is used, a
temporary restriction until cmocka 2.0 is more widely available across
distributions.

@section unit_tests_seam Testing static functions

Several of the functions under test are @c static and have no external linkage.
To reach them, the corresponding test compiles the whole translation unit in
directly with @c \#include (for example @c test_parse_pathlen.c does
@c \#include @c "parse.c"). That pulls in the file's other external references,
which a small companion "stubs" object then satisfies for the linker:

- @c test_stubs.c &mdash; the frontend globals and console/file helpers that
  @c get_audio.c drags in.
- @c parse_test_stubs.c &mdash; the console/file helpers that @c parse.c drags
  in (@c parse.c defines the frontend global-config blocks itself, so those are
  not re-stubbed).

libmp3lame supplies the real @c lame_* API. Where a test needs to observe
behaviour that the return value alone cannot reveal (such as a parser spinning
rather than returning), it interposes a libc call with the linker's
@c --wrap mechanism.

@section unit_tests_list The tests

- @c test_sanity.c &mdash; harness smoke test (@ref test_sanity.c).
- @c test_get_audio_aiff.c &mdash; AIFF FORM-size underflow guard in
  @c parse_aiff_header() (@ref test_get_audio_aiff.c).
- @c test_parse_pathlen.c &mdash; positional input/output filename length bound
  in @c set_path_arg() (@ref test_parse_pathlen.c).
- @c test_merge_argv.c &mdash; argument-vector sizing and the @c merge_argv()
  count clamp (@ref test_merge_argv.c).
*/
